. Prothorax (
Figs 7, 8
, 
13, 14
) yellow with central part posterior pronotal lobe black, lapels brown, anterior pronotal lobe black except lower lateral part, which has small black streak at anterior carina (
Fig. 7
). Lower cervical spur well developed. Notopleural projection (
Fig 8
), present in form of rounded bulge fused with lateral part anterior pronotal lobe. Posterior pronotal lobe with short rounded lapels just separated from short but broad central part with lateral parts produced as pointed almost triangular horns directed up and slightly upwards (
Figs. 13, 14
). Synthorax (
Figs 19, 20
) with pair yellowish antehumeral stripes, not quite reaching level of apex of antealar triangle. Lateral markings of synthorax similar to male but black mark on mesepimeron above metapleural suture isolated from black mark beside antealar carina. Left anterior leg missing below coxa Wings with arculus at Ax 2, 17 (left) or 18 (right) Px in Fw, 15 Px in Hw. IR 
3
distal to subnodus. Pt covering from one to one and ca two thirds underlying cells
